    "## 4. Merge taxi + weather and prepare the modeling dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "Project 2 requires **one combined dataset** made from taxi features plus climate features.  \n",
    "We combine January, March, and May taxi data, merge on date, fill missing weather values, and define:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Target:** `trip_duration_min`\n",
    "- **Features:** taxi numeric fields + weather numeric fields\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4.1 Define feature lists and month-prep helper\n",
    "Create reusable logic for weather merge, type coercion, and missing-value handling."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### 4.1.1 Reload month frames when needed\n",
    "If cells were rerun and cleanup removed the month DataFrames, reload them from parquet."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import gc\n",
    "\n",
    "if \"jan\" not in globals() or \"mar\" not in globals() or \"may\" not in globals():\n",
    "    jan = pd.read_parquet(jan_path)\n",
    "    mar = pd.read_parquet(mar_path)\n",
    "    may = pd.read_parquet(may_path)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### 4.1.2 Define model feature groups\n",
    "Set taxi features, target variable, and weather features used for downstream training."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "taxi_feature_cols = [\n",
    "    \"VendorID\", \"RatecodeID\", \"PULocationID\", \"DOLocationID\", \"payment_type\",\n",
    "    \"passenger_count\", \"trip_distance\", \"fare_amount\", \"tip_amount\", \"total_amount\",\n",
    "    \"pickup_hour\", \"pickup_weekday\", \"pickup_day\", \"pickup_month\",\n",
    "]\n",
    "target_col = \"trip_duration_min\"\n",
    "\n",
    "weather_feature_cols = [c for c in weather.columns if c != \"date\" and weather[c].notna().any()]\n",
    "weather_medians = {c: pd.to_numeric(weather[c], errors=\"coerce\").median() for c in weather_feature_cols}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### 4.1.3 Create month-to-model transformation helper\n",
    "This helper merges daily weather into taxi rows, enforces numeric dtypes, and drops rows missing required fields."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def build_month_model_df(df: pd.DataFrame) -> pd.DataFrame:\n",
    "    out = df.merge(weather[[\"date\"] + weather_feature_cols], left_on=\"pickup_date\", right_on=\"date\", how=\"left\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    for col in weather_feature_cols:\n",
    "        out[col] = pd.to_numeric(out[col], errors=\"coerce\").fillna(weather_medians[col])\n",
    "\n",
    "    keep_cols = taxi_feature_cols + weather_feature_cols + [target_col, \"pickup_date\"]\n",
    "    out = out.loc[:, keep_cols]\n",
    "\n",
    "    for col in taxi_feature_cols + weather_feature_cols + [target_col]:\n",
    "        out[col] = pd.to_numeric(out[col], errors=\"coerce\", downcast=\"float\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    required_cols = taxi_feature_cols + [target_col, \"pickup_date\"]\n",
    "    out = out.dropna(subset=required_cols)\n",
    "    return out"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4.2 Build monthly model-ready frames\n",
    "Apply the same processing logic independently to Jan/Mar/May."
   ]
